<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> en-US</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Thu, 14 Sep 2023 13:00:10 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Honda's adorable '80s microscooter is back and electrified for the 21st century]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>那不是 Photoshop——它应该看起来像那样。这是本田的 Motocompacto，一款复古的全电动骑行车，其灵感来自 80 年代短命的本田 Motocompo 踏板车，我很遗憾地说我有点喜欢它。</p><p>折叠起来的车辆类似于 Costco 的折叠桌之一，但底部有小铝轮。要将其改造成一辆踏板车，您可以延长车把、座椅和后轮，然后骑上类似于自行车的东西。 （为了让您对设计有所了解，这个东西只有三英尺多长。） </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/6846a470-5277-11ee-8cd0-a2d77d1088c3" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/6846a470-5277-11ee-8cd0-a2d77d1088c3" style="height:1700px;width:2667px;" alt="图为折叠的本田 Motocompacto。" data-uuid="078e4ce7-6e08-33cd-882a-2c19bfd45657"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">本田</div></figure><p>本田表示，其铝制车架和车轮使其保持“轻量化”，但 41 磅的重量与普通电动自行车处于同一重量级别，并且续航里程“长达 12 英里”，但它也无法让您走得太远。当它的12英里续航里程用完后，它可以在3.5小时内重新充满电，这是一个相当长的时间，但至少它配备了一个车载充电器，可供您插入110V插座。</p><p>这款踏板车的设计易于携带到车辆或公共交通工具上，这对于想要享受电动自行车或踏板车的便利性但又不想整天将其安全锁定的麻烦的城市居民来说可能是一个巨大的卖点。这是本田<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-03-23-honda-cr-electric-dirt-bike.html">大力推动电动汽车发展的</a>一部分，本田的目标是到 2040 年用电池电动和燃料电池电动汽车取代其整个产品线。 </p><div id="2c58f03bc7b8439e805f7c34d4679b19"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/XzkSthZHRiI?si=5XkeK8yTzkrWc3mp" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p>本田 Motocompacto 将于 11 月开始在 Motocompacto.com 以及本田和讴歌经销商处独家发售，售价“低于 995 美元”。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/hondas-adorable-80s-microscooter-is-back-and-electrified-for-the-21st- century-130010531.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/hondas-adorable-80s-microscooter-is-back-and-electrified-for-the-21st-century-130010531.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> df5c9ee1-beb0-4de9-abdf-f5cb04a301d5</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 13:00:10 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694642026</ingested><modified> 2023-09-13T21:53:52+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[Environment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="1700" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/6846a470-5277-11ee-8cd0-a2d77d1088c3" width="2667"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1700" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/43199540-5277-11ee-afdd-89a6eb009673" width="2667"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Honda]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Honda Motocompacto pictured.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Honda Motocompacto ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best air fryers for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>您是否对空气炸锅很感兴趣，但担心您可能会得到另一个不幸的厨房小玩意，占用您小厨房的空间？我们随时为您提供帮助。空气炸锅有多种不同的形状和尺寸，一旦您了解了它的功能，它就可以成为许多厨房的多功能补充。去年，空气炸锅的形状和尺寸已经确定，就像之前的速溶锅一样，它是一种厨房小工具，经常出现在黑色星期五或黄金周等主要在线促销活动上。</p><p>事实证明，这一功能非常受欢迎，以至于一些一体式厨房电器，甚至传统烤箱现在都配备了空气炸锅设置。这种多功能性对于空间较小的小型厨房非常有用。有些空气炸锅提供两个不同的烹饪区域，这意味着您可以同步烹饪两个不同的食物，而无需让任何东西冷却。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>首先我们要明确一件事：这不是油炸。并不真地。空气炸锅更像是较小的对流烤箱，通常是豆荚形的。大多数工作原理是将加热元件和风扇结合起来，这意味着热空气通常比其他方法可以更好地使食物外部酥脆。它们通常能达到比烤面包机更高的最高温度——这也是其吸引力的一部分。</p><p>对于大多数食谱来说，一层薄薄的油（通常是喷洒的）有助于更好地复制油炸的外观和感觉。然而，它的味道很少会像油炸版本一样。不过，不要因此而放弃，因为空气炸锅有多种形式，结合了其他烹饪过程中的一些最佳部分，并将它们组合成一种节能的晚餐烹饪方式。或者早餐。或者午餐。</p><h2>空气炸锅要注意什么</h2><h3>对流烤箱</h3><p>您可以将大多数空气炸锅分为两种类型，每种类型都有不同的优缺点。对流烤箱通常是具有空气炸锅功能和特点的烤箱。它们可能有更高的温度设置，以确保食物变脆并烹饪得更像真正的油炸食物。大多数对流烤箱都比专用空气炸锅大，这违背了那些希望缩小烹饪器具表面积的人的一些目的。尽管如此，它们通常更通用，具有多种烹饪功能，并且大多数对温度、时间甚至风扇速度都有更精细的控制。</p><p>如果您有一个像样的对流烤箱，您可能永远不需要内置烤箱。它们通常有足够的容量来处理烤肉、整只鸡或托盘烘烤，并且可以根据容量进行更多烹饪，这使得它们比豆荚形竞争对手更通用。</p><p>另一方面是你需要厨房里的柜台空间来容纳它们。这还意味着您可以使用您可能已经拥有的传统烤箱配件，例如烤盘或蛋糕罐。</p><h3>荚形空气炸锅</h3><p>荚形空气炸锅<strong>&nbsp;</strong>当您想到“空气炸锅”时，您会想到这些。它们看起来像一个很酷的太空时代厨房小工具，比水壶大，但比烤箱小。许多人在烹饪时使用抽屉来盛放食材，通常是网状床单或更坚固的不粘托盘，带有孔以让热空气流通。除了少数例外，大多数都要求您在烹饪食物时打开抽屉，翻转或摇动半熟的食物，以确保热量和气流均匀分布到所有东西。</p><p>这是一些警告之一。大多数豆荚形空气炸锅（也有少数例外）没有窗口来查看食物的烹饪情况，因此您需要在烹饪时仔细检查食物，打开设备检查进度。篮式空气炸锅通常也消耗更少的能源——加热空间更小——而且许多都有可以直接放入洗碗机的部件。</p><p>一些较大的豆荚形空气炸锅提供两个独立的隔间，这对于计划用该设备烹饪整顿饭的人特别有用。你可以煮几个美味的鸡翅或鸡柳，同时为每个人准备足够的冷冻薯条或蔬菜。当然，这些选项会占用更多空间，而且它们通常很重，无法将它们存放在其他地方的橱柜或架子上。</p><p>如前所述，您可能需要购买额外的东西才能使这些荚式油炸机按照您希望的方式工作。一些较大的制造商，如飞利浦和 Ninja，提供方便的附加功能，但您必须付费。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-03/fcbb58a0-a9d4-11ec-97f7-1be0d263a8a8" alt="女人用空气炸锅华夫饼供应炸鸡" data-uuid="7660e083-5f6a-33ba-b446-55741911b1bf"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">法比安·庞塞（Fabián Ponce）来自盖蒂图片社</div></figure><h2>空气炸锅的优点和缺点</h2><p>除了各个型号的优点和缺点之外，空气炸锅从一开始就非常易于使用。大多数型号都配有方便的烹饪时间手册，涵盖了您将要空气炸制的大多数主要食物，因此即使是初学者也可以掌握这些机器。</p><p>早期的卖点之一是能够用比油炸等其他方法更少的脂肪来烹饪薯条、鸡翅、冷冻食品和其他美食，油炸使食物变得最脆。由于空气炸锅通过循环热空气来工作，因此托盘和烹饪盘上都有孔，这些孔也可以让肉中的油脂排出，这意味着当您最终将食物装盘时，脂肪会减少，食物也会更脆。对于大多数烹饪情况，您可能需要在食物上轻轻喷洒植物油。如果不这样做，东西就有可能燃烧或烧焦。油会使食物表面保持湿润，我们建议在烹饪过程中翻转食物时喷洒少许油以提亮食物。</p><p>大多数空气炸锅都很容易清洁——尤其是与浅炸锅或深炸锅相比。稍后我们将介绍清洁指南。</p><p>由于加热空间较小，空气炸锅在烹饪食物时通常比烤箱等大型电器更节能。如果您没有烤箱，空气炸锅的价格要便宜得多，尤其是炸荚式炸锅。</p><p>然而，也有一些缺点。虽然空气炸锅很容易使用，但需要时间才能掌握。即使是最简单的食物，例如鸡块、冷冻炸薯条或球芽甘蓝，您也可以调整烹饪时间。如果你是那种喜欢从互联网上寻找灵感的人，根据我们的经验，你几乎可以把他们的时间抛到九霄云外。空气炸锅有很多选择，加热速度和热量分布等因素可以而且将会影响烹饪。</p><p>空气炸锅还存在空间限制。这不是 TARDIS——它的空间比大多数传统烤箱和许多深油炸锅要小。如果您有一个更大的家庭，您可能会想要一台大容量的空气炸锅 - 可能是一个有多个烹饪区域的空气炸锅。</p><p>您可能还很难将许多食物煮熟，因为加热设置会在菜肴完全煮熟之前很久就将其表面煮熟。如果您打算烹饪整只鸡或烤肉，请准备一个肉类温度计！</p><h2>最佳空气炸锅配件</h2><p>除了制造商提供的官方配件外，还可以尝试使用硅胶头工具。 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAed3N9FiYOffc86Osee6J_2C_kQYw6soIkNXCm5Oegqs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSilicone-Non-Stick-Resistant-Grilling-Tortillas%2Fdp%2FB08RHQ5S95">夹子</a>是理想的选择，硅胶抹刀也是理想的选择，可以轻轻地松开可能卡在空气炸锅侧面的食物。这些<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlDUEZRNFlEP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRhLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4ZGZiMGUzNS0wZDU5LTQxYWMtYTZjZC1iOWFmNWE0YmRhZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAYNgS5wcy4fcn6uBAM9aw93W-eucDE-uD5ICTwC6BhkQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09CPFQ4YD">硅胶垫</a>还有助于防止东西粘在某些空气炸锅的电线架上。它们有孔，以确保加热的空气仍然能够在食物周围循环。</p><p>当您整理剩下的饭菜时， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb89xwPa_ZnOogFhA0EVy2dB8ESiC4WCV1_WlplQoB_d&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJoyhalo-Silicone-Resistant-Non-Slip-Coasters%2Fdp%2FB08FJ75771">硅胶三脚架</a>也可用于放置任何煮熟的食物。如果您发现自己需要喷油，但不想反复购买小瓶，您可以将您最喜欢的植物油倒入这样的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZCIBvcZHmytRJWD2WelnjmHCh25m1eXEVW0v-mVQ5m7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMasterClass-Stainless-Steel-Mister-Bottle%2Fdp%2FB0001IX1EI%3F">永久喷雾器</a>中。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-11/c868fae0-507d-11ec-87ef-c140215603f6" alt="用空气炸锅炸薯条。健康减脂食物" data-uuid="91fb56b5-6091-3bd2-a55a-6694a5eeee08"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> yulka3ice 来自 Getty Images</div></figure><h2>如何清洁空气炸锅</h2><p>我们在这里保持简单的清理。是的，您可以使用杂货店的强力清洁剂，它们可能会损坏空气炸锅的表面。同样，金属刷子或刷子可能会剥落不粘涂层。请记住拔掉设备插头并让它完全冷却。</p><p>从里面取出托盘、篮子和其他所有东西。如果制造商说这些零件可用洗碗机清洗——并且您有洗碗机——那么工作就基本完成了。</p><p>否则，用温水和 Dawn 或其他强力洗洁精混合手洗每个部件。使用软毛刷清除任何表面上粘附的面包屑、油腻沉积物或食物残渣。记得冲洗所有东西。否则，你的下一批鸡翅可能会有温和的黎明余味。相信我们。</p><p>使用超细纤维布擦拭外部部件和手柄，这些部件在重复使用后也可能会变得有点脏。这对于烤箱式空气炸锅特别有用——用布擦拭内侧。</p><p>如果 Dawn 无法去除油渍，请尝试将少量小苏打与足够的水混合制成糊状，然后涂抹，以免其渗入任何电气部件或加热元件。让它工作几秒钟，然后用湿布擦掉油渍。冲洗布并再次擦拭所有东西，这样您就可以为下次需要空气炸锅做好准备了。</p><h2>如何找到空气炸锅食谱</h2><p>除了薯条、鸡块和冷冻饺子之外，还有几种方法可以为您的新空气炸锅找到食谱。首先，我们发现空气炸锅的使用手册通常包含烹饪指南和食谱建议，供您在新的厨房小工具中进行测试。这些的好处是它们是为您的空气炸锅型号制造的，这意味着成功几乎是有保证的。然而，他们往往有点缺乏想象力。</p><p>许多顶级食谱网站和门户网站都不乏空气炸锅食谱，在谷歌上搜索您最喜欢的美食并在搜索字符串末尾添加“空气炸锅”一词也没有什么坏处。我们从<em>Delish</em>中选择了一些可靠的选择，它还有一个方便的空气炸锅时间<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.delish.com/kitchen-tools/cookware-reviews/a35686392/air-fryer-conversion/">转换器</a>，用于更改烤箱和传统炸锅食谱。</p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/collection/air-fryer-recipes"><em>BBC Good Food</em></a>也值得浏览，寻找一些简单的想法， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2Nvb2tpbmcubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4ZGZiMGUzNS0wZDU5LTQxYWMtYTZjZC1iOWFmNWE0YmRhZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAQlYZaY4TNa78tVAt9mFUeOlSWHXXGjsrTSZXBwIMML9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fcooking.nytimes.com%2F">NYT Cooking</a>也是如此，可以直接搜索空气炸锅建议。</p><p>如果您对空气炸锅有杀手级食谱或独特用途，请在评论中告诉我们。相当于速溶锅芝士蛋糕的空气炸锅是什么？我们准备尝试一下。</p><h2>整体最佳：Instant Vortex Plus</h2><p><core-commerce id="28dfb39e21804d3ebe87226f8674bac1" data-type="product-list"></p><p>您可能通过非常受欢迎的 Instant Pot 高压锅系列了解“Instant”品牌，但您是否知道该公司也生产出色的空气炸锅？配备 ClearCook 和 OdorErase 功能的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAV7QjhbAOnFWnCU6wdAgLMuYEzwivUl-pxjmwrjzveV0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FVortexTM-Fryer-ClearCook-OdorErase-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB096N28SZP%3F">Instant Vortex Plus</a>给我们留下了特别深刻的印象，它具有清晰的观察窗，让您在烹饪食物时可以看到空气炸篮，此外还有一个除臭过滤器。在我们的测试中，我们发现它并没有完全消除气味，但与我们的 Breville 智能烤箱空气相比，它的烟味似乎明显减少。我们喜欢它易于使用的直观控制装置、易于清洁的不粘抽屉篮以及宽敞的内部空间 - 它足够大，可以容纳四个鸡腿。此外，这款首选加热速度非常快，几乎不需要预热时间。</p><p>一个稍微更实惠的选择是其前身 Instant Vortex Plus 6 夸脱。它没有观察窗和除臭过滤器，但仍然具有相同的直观控制面板和宽敞的不粘内部。如果您想要更大的选择，Instant 还提供 10 夸脱型号的 Instant Vortex Plus，该型号具有观察窗和烤肉架功能。</p><h2>最佳双区：Ninja Foodi 双区空气炸锅</h2><p><core-commerce id="0bffe0c768194dffa9b195d0edc6c707" data-type="product-list"></p><p>大多数机器一次只能制作一种食物，但<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQ9JPd0SJI2oWJQSo9MpuTS_3vnKc7tbM4QkD6TcXHGs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FNinja-DZ201-2-Basket-Technology-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB096X9LGJ1%3F">Ninja 的双区</a>数字空气炸锅可以同时处理两种完全不同的食物。这款双篮空气炸锅有 8 夸脱和 10 夸脱容量可供选择，但结构并不紧凑，因此对于厨房较小的人来说，它不是一个好的选择。然而，如果您有柜台空间，它可能是最好的投资空气炸锅，特别是如果您为一个大家庭做饭。您可以使用完全不同的烹饪模式同时准备两种完全不同的食物，例如鸡柳和布朗尼蛋糕，或者使用 Match Cook 以相同的方式准备双篮子中的食物。加热区是独立的，所以如果您只想一侧填满炸薯条而另一侧空着，您也可以这样做。</p><p>我们欣赏 Ninja 空气炸锅的加热速度有多快（几乎没有预热时间）以及它的运行相对安静。它还具有名为“智能完成”的功能，可自动调整烹饪时间，以便第一个室中的炸鸡大腿和第二个室中的芦笋同时完成，因此您无需等待餐点的一部分在对方变冷的时候做好准备。一般来说，双区空气炸锅功能对于大多数人来说并不是必需的，但那些经常做饭的人会大量使用像 Ninja Foodi 这样的机器。</p><h2>最佳预算：Instant Vortex Mini</h2><p><core-commerce id="0e876c8e59c147449c8907ab1a9b0bc2" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9JbnN0YW50LUN1c3RvbWl6YWJsZS1Qcm9ncmFtcy1Ob25zdGljay1EaXNod2FzaGVyLVNhZmUvZHAvQjA4WVMyWlo5Ny8_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby00YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOGRmYjBlMzUtMGQ1OS00MWFjLWE2Y2QtYjlhZjVhNGJkYWQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAbxiuo0cZ3liC7ZeaAATWKJ7PfHsqBSVZURtuASXUIhR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FInstant-Customizable-Programs-Nonstick-Dishwasher-Safe%2Fdp%2FB08YS2ZZ97%2F%3Fth%3D1">Instant Vortex Mini</a>不仅价格实惠，价格为 60 美元（而且您经常可以以更低的价格找到它），而且它也是此列表中最好的小型空气炸锅。大多数空气炸锅会占用大量宝贵的台面空间，但这款两夸脱的型号非常适合那些没有太多闲置空间的人。 Vortex Mini 可以空气煎、烘烤、烘烤和重新加热，您可以使用触摸屏中间的旋钮控制温度和烹饪时间。与我们测试的其他一些更昂贵的空气炸锅（具有多种模式和设置）不同，Vortex Mini 的使用非常简单。只需插入电源，按您选择的预设烹饪方法，自定义温度和烹饪时间，然后按“开始”即可。机器会在循环过程中发出蜂鸣声，让您知道何时翻转食物，完成后它会再次发出蜂鸣声。</p><p>可以说，Vortex Mini 最大的缺点也是它的最大优势。它是如此紧凑，以至于烹饪不止一种东西或很多一种东西并不容易。但我可以毫无问题地将整块豆腐切成方块（有一点重叠）并为自己和我的未婚夫重新加热（并重新酥脆）剩菜。总的来说，对于那些预算紧张和厨房狭小的人来说，这款紧凑型空气炸锅将是无与伦比的。</p><h2>最佳多功能空气炸锅：Breville Smart Oven Air Fryer Pro</h2><p><core-commerce id="83f0d894151241ffb62af1a43b4dbd1f" data-type="product-list"></p><p>听着，大多数人不需要<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUxrtKpli_MsWp5g9aqLWx0yvD9Bzh4J8wgvardDahZ-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBreville-BOV900BSS-Convection-Brushed-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB01N5UPTZS">Breville Smart Oven Air Fryer Pro</a> 。但如果您喜欢做饭、有一个大家庭或举办很多聚会，那么您可能会大量使用这台机器。这款不锈钢台面烤箱是一头野兽，尺寸为一立方英尺，因此请准备好在厨房中为其留出一些空间。但它的尺寸使其能够烹饪整只 14 磅重的火鸡，并可以在其中放入 5 夸脱的荷兰烤箱和 9 x 13 平底锅等物品。这款大型空气炸锅基本上就像第二个烤箱，如果您的主烤箱无法使用，甚至可以用作主烤箱。</p><p>作为此列表中最好的空气炸锅烤箱，它的功能非常强大，而且它的尺寸也很有帮助，因为您可以将食物摊开以确保食物尽可能酥脆。它还可以帮助您一次烹饪很多份食物，如果您要准备早午餐百吉饼、聚会开胃菜或家庭晚餐配菜等零食，这会更容易。除了空气炸锅外，它还有多种其他烹饪模式，包括吐司、烧烤、烘烤、披萨、脱水、慢煮和发酵。尽管有“智能”的绰号，但该型号没有应用程序连接 - 但如果您升级到<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Breville;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c0ca87c7-692e-4b52-8410-9ea74ef1a5a6&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Breville&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAaUrVCOat1Tdkav86QXaIcZ37-kvfn35fsguzZmZUKNx&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.breville.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fproducts%2Fovens%2Fbov950.html%3Fsku%3DBOV950BSS1BUS1">Joule</a> ，您就可以获得该功能。这样您就可以在食物准备好时收到推送通知，并且配套应用程序还具有您可以遵循的指导食谱。毫不奇怪，像大多数 Breville 小工具一样，Joule 和标准智能烤箱空气炸锅 Pro 都相当昂贵，分别为 500 美元和 400 美元。但如果您想为您的厨房添加多功能机器，Breville 可以满足您的需求。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/best-air-fryers-133047180.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-air-fryers-133047180.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8dfb0e35-0d59-41ac-a6cd-b9af5a4bdad8</guid><dc:creator>马特·史密斯、妮可·李、瓦伦蒂娜·帕拉迪诺</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 12:55:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694696108</ingested><modified> 2023-09-14T12:55:17+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Food & Cooking]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mat Smith]]></category><media:content height="1300" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/66d22900-d227-11ed-92f5-34acaf80a4bd" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1300" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/66d22900-d227-11ed-92f5-34acaf80a4bd" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Best air fryer]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Best air fryer]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google expands its iFixit partnership by offering parts for Pixel Tablet repairs]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Google 于 2022 年中期<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-repair-diy-parts-ifixit-182931322.html">与 iFixit 合作，</a>为您提供可用于维修 Pixel 手机的正品组件。现在看来，两党的合作伙伴关系已经扩大了。据<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://9to5google.com/2023/09/14/pixel-tablet-repair-parts-ifixit/" data-original-link="https://9to5google.com/2023/09/14/pixel-tablet-repair-parts-ifixit/"><em>9to5Google</em></a>报道，iFixit 已<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Google_Pixel_Tablet" data-original-link="https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Google_Pixel_Tablet">开始销售</a>谷歌 6 月份发布的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-tablet-review-clever-accessories-transform-an-unexciting-tablet-070147119.html">Pixel 平板电脑</a>的多个原装零部件。现在出售的最昂贵的组件之一是平板电脑的后壳，售价 200 美元，配有三个麦克风、天线、带指纹解锁的电源按钮和音量控制。</p><p>如果你的平板电脑电池坏了，你现在可以花 67 美元购买正品更换电池，而更换有问题的后置摄像头则需要花费 25 美元。更换一个扬声器以及更换设备的 USB-C 端口也将花费 25 美元。但如果是平板电脑的屏幕需要更换，则需要支付 200 美元或更多。您可以按照该价格仅购买该部件（包括前置玻璃数字转换器屏幕、10.95 英寸 2560 x 1600 像素 LCD 和 8 兆像素前置摄像头），也可以购买包含打开所需工具的包购买平板电脑需加 6 美元。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>当然，iFixit 不仅仅销售零件：其<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:5;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Google_Pixel_Tablet" data-original-link="https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Google_Pixel_Tablet">Pixel 平板电脑门户</a>还包含有关如何修复其销售的每个组件的模型的指南。如果您想确保自己做的是正确的事情，即使您非常擅长摆弄电子产品，也可以遵循它们。除了谷歌之外，iFixit 还与其他品牌建立了合作伙伴关系，其中包括<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-self-repair-program-galaxy-phone-ifixit-160016344.html">三星</a>，该公司去年与该指导网站合作，为其 Galaxy 设备推出了“自行修复”计划。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/google-expands-its-ifixit-partnership-by-offering-parts-for-pixel-tablet-repairs-122600528.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-expands-its-ifixit-partnership-by-offering-parts-for-pixel-tablet-repairs-122600528.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 08dee213-b7f0-445b-9eb4-3ae0a882e162</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 12:26:00 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694692606</ingested><modified> 2023-09-14T11:56:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="1166" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/09b88e30-52f1-11ee-bf7b-fb13a3dc78b9" width="1750"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1166" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/09b88e30-52f1-11ee-bf7b-fb13a3dc78b9" width="1750"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A tablet on top of a wooden table.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google Pixel tablet]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[HP's $5,000 Spectre Fold might be the best flexible-screen laptop yet]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>早在2020年，联想就发布了<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lenovo-thinkpad-x1-fold-foldable-pc-review-specs-price-181519620.html">首款配备柔性显示屏的笔记本电脑</a>。去年，华硕通过<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zenbook-17-fold-oled-review-specs-price-great-screen-now-do-the-keyboard-131547070.html">Zenbook 17 Fold OLED 增加了这一类别。</a>现在，惠普正在尝试 Spectre Fold，在检查了发送给媒体的三个预生产样品之一后，感觉这无疑是该技术迄今为止的最佳应用。</p><p> Spectre Fold 最引人注目的是它的设计。惠普成功缩小了边框，并消除了我们在可折叠 ZenBook 上看到的几乎所有厚重感。其 17 英寸 2560 x 1920 OLED 显示屏完全打开，整个设备看起来就像任何其他高级平板电脑（除了它非常大），这是一个惊喜。 Spectre Fold 厚度为 8.5 毫米，非常纤薄，并且采用轻质镁机身，重量仅为 2.86 磅（1.3 千克），比华硕 2022 年推出的产品轻了整整一磅。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="905189176c164382ab0faf6bf606273f"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/n18BSmmYV9U?si=0iwGmvyPgHUI8XTy" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p> Spectre Fold 的显示屏看起来也很棒。该面板由 LG 制造，基本上没有折痕（除非你从某个角度看得很仔细），同时拥有高达 500 尼特的标称亮度，并通过 VESA True Black HDR 500 认证。为了满足您的所有视频会议需求，HP 配备了锐利的 5-MP 红外网络摄像头，支持一些巧妙的安全功能，例如隐私警报和自动离开检测。</p><p>还有一个光滑的支架，在不使用时可以与系统底部齐平。事实上，它看起来更像是一个简单的设计重点，而不是功能性的东西。几乎在任何地方，Spectre Fold 给人的感觉都与任何高端笔记本电脑一样时尚、精致。现在，这听起来可能不是一项重大成就，但考虑到我们在之前的竞争对手身上看到的尴尬，这绝非易事。我还很欣赏 ​​HP 如何提供方便的功能，例如物理网络摄像头快门开关和两个 Thunderbolt 4 端口。然后还有 Spectre Fold 的所有捆绑配件，其中包括磁性蓝牙键盘、手写笔（带有备用笔尖），甚至还有 USB-C 扩展坞集线器。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/e4ff9ad0-5272-11ee-b73a-ff0ce11d40ae" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/e4ff9ad0-5272-11ee-b73a-ff0ce11d40ae" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="惠普表示 Spectre Fold 是该公司首款三合一产品。" data-uuid="cdb223f8-d054-332c-b5c2-964ef6772d97"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>这让我想到了 Spectre Fold 的第二个优点，那就是它开箱即用，与所有配件都能很好地配合——我不需要搞乱蓝牙设置或其他任何东西。我刚刚启动笔记本电脑，翻转键盘侧面的开关，它们立即连接起来。与我在 Zenbook 17 Fold 上的体验相比，这是一个很大的进步，其不稳定的蓝牙迫使我定期手动修复其键盘。惠普还将该系统设计为具有 5 毫米的折叠半径，使键盘在旅行时可以整齐地嵌入笔记本电脑内。</p><p>但 Spectre Fold 最酷的地方（当然，除了它的显示屏）是你看不到的：一系列隐藏在系统边缘内的充电线圈。这使得键盘和手写笔（也通过磁性连接）在不使用时可以通过笔记本电脑的电池进行涓流充电，因此您永远不必担心自己给它们充电。不过，如果键盘由于某种原因没电了，惠普确实提供了一个特殊的 USB 电源适配器，您可以在紧要关头拿出来。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/5c0b86c0-5273-11ee-afdb-5243608922a0" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/5c0b86c0-5273-11ee-afdb-5243608922a0" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="通过向下滑动磁性键盘，Spectre Fold 会转变为展开模式，该模式具有惠普所称的" data-uuid="5c704c03-98b0-31d7-ad31-6d2c3d77a267"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>当然，显示屏是<em>最酷</em>的部分。 Spectre Fold 的可弯曲性使其成为惠普首款三合一产品，因为它可以转变为平板电脑、便携式一体化台式机和几种不同的笔记本电脑设置。平板电脑模式非常简单，而 AIO 模式允许您支撑显示屏，这样您就可以充分利用 17 英寸大显示屏（我希望在最近旅行时拥有它）。</p><p>作为笔记本电脑，您可以选择某种传统的翻盖式配置，将键盘放在显示屏的下半部分，而上半部分则提供 12.5 英寸的屏幕，这非常适合狭小的空间。或者，您可以将键盘向您的方向滑动以创建惠普所谓的扩展模式，这可能是我最喜欢的笔记本电脑位置。在此设置中，键盘的触摸板部分下降并提供更符合人体工程学的腕托。这样做还可以展示更多的折叠显示屏（总共约 14 英寸）或 HP 所说的“1.5 屏幕”。这为您提供了足够的空间，可以将电子邮件或聊天应用程序等内容放在下面，同时您可以在顶部打开更重要的项目。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/deef3780-5273-11ee-a5ff-be6d636dbd41" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/deef3780-5273-11ee-a5ff-be6d636dbd41" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Spectre Fold 具有内置支架，不使用时可与系统齐平，使其几乎完全消失。" data-uuid="c2f3151e-5b1d-3558-85ed-e99b39628dda"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>最后，还有扩展模式，您只需将键盘放在 Spectre Fold 前面的桌子上，即可完全访问 17 英寸屏幕，但处于弯曲的纵向方向。无论您喜欢哪种设置，笔记本电脑都会根据您当前的环境尽力为您提供尽可能大的显示屏。由于系统内部有更多的磁铁，键盘可以自然地吸附到这些不同的位置，从而带来令人惊讶的无缝体验。</p><p>诚然，即使这么早，我也注意到了一些小问题，比如从更锐利的角度观看时显示屏看起来更暗，这就是您在某些笔记本电脑模式中看到的情况。但即使在当今最好的柔性屏幕中，这也算是一个标准。此外，虽然迄今为止它的英特尔酷睿 i7-1250U、16GB 内存和 1TB 固态硬盘提供了相对快速的性能，但我并不期望它能在编辑视频甚至轻度游戏等方面发挥巨大的作用。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ae15e050-5273-11ee-bddd-3e6bbbd427b8" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ae15e050-5273-11ee-bddd-3e6bbbd427b8" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="在平板电脑模式下，Spectre Fold 看起来很像任何其他高端平板电脑，除了其巨大的 17 英寸柔性显示屏。" data-uuid="54db5786-b1e3-385e-bef2-449b0dac722a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>然而，Spectre Fold 的最大障碍是它的价格：5,000 美元。这甚至比售价 3,500 美元的华硕 Zenbook 17 Fold 还要贵，后者已经是一款极其昂贵的机器了。这足以让几乎每个人都无法接触到它，这绝对是令人失望的。但与此同时，惠普表示，它创造这个东西很大程度上只是为了展示该公司可以利用当今的尖端技术做些什么。当我将其更多地视为一个具有前瞻性的演示单元而不是人们实际要购买的东西时，我对其成本的不满就少了一些（哪怕只是一点点）。我还应该指出，尽管联想的第二款柔性屏笔记本电脑——17英寸ThinkPad X1 Fold——在一年多前就已经展示过，但仍然没有具体的发布日期。这恰恰表明，即使对于这种规模的公司来说，制造这样的系统是多么困难（联想和惠普是世界上最大的两家个人电脑供应商）。</p><p>也就是说，如果你愿意为这款产品支付几笔（或更多）租金，那么 Spectre Fold 的预订今天即可从百思买开始，预计将在 HP.com 和百思买上进行正式销售十月的某个时候。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/hps-5000-spectre-fold-might-be-the-best-flexible-screen-laptop-yet-120039948.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/hps-5000-spectre-fold-might-be-the-best-flexible-screen-laptop-yet-120039948.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5a192ebb-481a-4b58-8d9c-008940077cc2</guid><dc:creator>萨姆·卢瑟福</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 12:00:39 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694691807</ingested><modified> 2023-09-14T11:43:35+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/e4ff9ad0-5272-11ee-b73a-ff0ce11d40ae" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/268dd4d0-5273-11ee-bfba-5806e6efce18" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[HP's first flexible-screen laptop features a gorgeous 17-inch OLED from LG.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[HP Spectre Fold]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Samsung's Galaxy Watch 6 review: Evolution not revolution]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>三星 Galaxy Watch 6 相对于其前身 Galaxy Watch 5 进行了适度的升级。当然，它可能致力于改进一些健康跟踪功能。它甚至成功地为可穿戴设备提供了更时尚的设计，同时延长了电池寿命。但很明显，三星并不打算在这里重新发明轮子（而且他们<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-watch5-pro-130048911.html">通常不会这样做</a>）。原因也很容易理解，因为上一代已经<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-5-pro-review-battery-life-specs-durability-180052187.html">相当不错了</a>。</p><p>在今年的更新中，三星将重点放在扩展其以健康为中心的功能上。其中包括增强的个性化睡眠指导和见解、在跑步过程中个性化心率区训练的能力、为田径跑步者量身定制的改进的 GPS 跟踪、锻炼应用程序的进一步定制以及包含不规则心率节律通知，仅举几例。当然，需要注意的是，Watch 6 的前身将可以访问所有这些更新，可以追溯到 Watch 4。因此，如果您拥有前两种型号之一，则可能不需要升级。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="d69981f0620a4fd8a576bfffdfbf0db7" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>尽管如此，Galaxy Watch 6 的适度改进使其能够跟上该领域的领先者。例如，它现在可以与 Fitbit 的高级睡眠分析功能并肩作战。新的心脏健康工具还赋予该手表苹果和 Pixel 智能手表的心电图监测能力。同时，改进的跑步指导使其更接近 Garmin 提供的手表。</p><h2>设计和电池寿命</h2><div id="705203888b8240d5ad6cf630d35e0fe6"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/unjnhj7-UCc?si=D8YZkXSHbrPDjohC" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p> Watch 6 的机械<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-6-hands-on-the-spinning-bezels-triumphant-return-110047694.html">无边框版</a>40 毫米型号售价为 299 美元，有石墨色和金色可供选择； 43 毫米版本也有银色可供选择，价格略高，为 329 美元。它可能没有经典款的旋转边框，但它确实有一个数字边框，可以让你滚动浏览最常用的小部件，如睡眠、锻炼和天气，而无需浏览菜单。</p><p>在 Watch 6 中，三星还推出了一项名为“一键式”的新设计功能，只需按一下按钮即可轻松更换表带，以满足您不断变化的风格需求。我个人非常喜欢石墨运动表带和齐平的圆形表面，这给手表带来了更时尚的感觉。</p><p> Watch 6 还拥有更鲜艳、更高分辨率的显示屏，峰值亮度达到 2,000 尼特，高于上一代型号的最高 1,000 尼特。屏幕也增大了 20%，更易于阅读文本。当我们的副评论编辑 Cherlynn Low 评测时，Watch 5 的常亮显示 (AOD) 功能很快耗尽了 Watch 5 的电池寿命，但我整天戴着 Watch 6 并没有遇到类似的问题。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/3cde3290-5181-11ee-bfcf-7dab6699ac4b" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/3cde3290-5181-11ee-bfcf-7dab6699ac4b" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="三星 Galaxy Watch 6 表盘" data-uuid="af7134ea-7b7e-36eb-9e0c-f80ed6542c08"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>Galaxy Watch 6 配备了<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcpF4D5TPv5B1fp59HpThqaN_0JAroohq3FXKwI8DsCY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.samsung.com%2Fglobal%2Fsamsung-galaxy-watch6-and-galaxy-watch6-classic-inspiring-your-best-self-day-and-night" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://news.samsung.com/global/samsung-galaxy-watch6-and-galaxy-watch6-classic-inspiring-your-best-self-day-and-night">更大的电池</a>，以支持今年更大、更亮的显示屏。三星声称，这款手表在 AOD 打开时可运行长达 30 小时，在关闭时可运行长达 40 小时。对于忙碌的人们来说，这是理想的选择，他们希望保证手表在工作八小时后，在去健身房之前可以正常工作，然后再进行睡眠跟踪。使用手表一两天后（主要用于锻炼跟踪），我可以使用快速充电功能在 30 分钟内将手表充电至约 80%，或几乎充满，至少再增加 8 小时的使用时间每次的电池寿命。然而，任何可穿戴设备的电池寿命往往会根据使用程度而波动。</p><h2>健康监测与追踪</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/9a0e6610-5181-11ee-839f-438203b82938" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/9a0e6610-5181-11ee-839f-438203b82938" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="三星 Galaxy Watch 6 表盘" data-uuid="d3f33aff-545a-38f0-8350-df93cdd05313"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>Watch 6 具有<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL25ld3Muc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vZ2xvYmFsL3NhbXN1bmctYnJpbmdzLWlycmVndWxhci1oZWFydC1yaHl0aG0tbm90aWZpY2F0aW9uLXRvLWdhbGF4eS13YXRjaC1pbi0xMy1tYXJrZXRzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJkODcxZTE2YS1hN2YzLTQ0NDYtYWJiZS00MjA0ODNmOGMwODgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATppIgglvK2YW0DkLvgbhhX5tCqmXTTjI4JHKtdasFip&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.samsung.com%2Fglobal%2Fsamsung-brings-irregular-heart-rhythm-notification-to-galaxy-watch-in-13-markets" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://news.samsung.com/global/samsung-brings-irregular-heart-rhythm-notification-to-galaxy-watch-in-13-markets">不规则心律通知 (IHRN) 功能</a>，该功能<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-galaxy-watch-will-soon-be-able-to-alert-wearers-to-irregular-heart-rhythms-161545939.html">对三星来说</a>是一项新功能，但多年来一直<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-pixel-watch-now-offers-overnight-blood-oxygen-tracking-170050532.html">在竞争设备上</a>使用。 FDA 支持的 IHRN 工具可检测提示心房颤动 (AFib) 的心电图活动，这种情况通常会先于中风或心力衰竭发生。该功能已获得 FDA 批准，可在后台持续监测用户的心脏活动。因为我没有 AFib，所以无法测试此功能以查看它是否可以准确检测不规则的心脏活动。 This, coupled with the traditional blood pressure monitoring, blood oxygen monitoring, body composition measuring tool, and EKG readings, add to Samsung&#39;s overall pool of individualized health data tracking that can easily be accessed in reports on a paired Android phone and shared with a healthcare provider or family member.</p><p> I do wish that after running a standard EKG reading, the language around heart health was less jargony. The &quot;sinus rhythm detected&quot; pop-up could easily be misunderstood, but in reality just means your heart activity is normal. That aside, Samsung did cover its own back. With each EKG cycle you run, a pop up disclosure repeats: “this wearable does not detect heart attacks.” The addition of the IHRN feature on the Watch 6 is in line with the company&#39;s attempt to offer more useful cardiovascular insights to users.</p><p> Expanding its range of tracking features, Samsung built upon its existing <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-galaxy-watch-5-will-soon-offer-temperature-based-period-tracking-113535293.html">menstrual cycle predictions tool introduced in the Watch 5</a> . This includes the skin temperature reading and sensor technology from the last-gen model, which records measurements during sleep. This addition aids in monitoring your monthly period, ovulation cycle and fertility windows. For it to be useful, though, the tool needs consistent data input by a user so that its predictions get smarter. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/b0d0a980-5181-11ee-bff4-0d65df3ee6fa" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/b0d0a980-5181-11ee-bff4-0d65df3ee6fa" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 face" data-uuid="d5766e58-f8aa-38e6-b1f2-f25c4d284802"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>Powered by Natural Cycles, a period tracking app, the new dedicated watch face makes it easy to input daily symptoms, which are not all necessarily tethered to a menstrual cycle. It can track everything from mood changes to physical conditions like cramping and bloating to logging sexual activity. All that data, in aggregate, can help Samsung&#39;s app predict when a period will start and end, fertility windows, and when ovulation is expected to kick in. This is all great in theory, but if you&#39;re not great at logging daily, you might end up like me, with outdated predictions that your period was supposed to start but never did.</p><p> The new watch also comes with a fall detection feature that has a built-in SOS tool that shares a user&#39;s location with an emergency service line or emergency contact of your choosing when a hard fall is detected. You have to manually set up this feature and select when the watch should detect falls – it can be on all the time, during workouts, or quote, “during any activity, or movements not registered as exercise.” Once a fall is detected, Samsung says the device can take up to 30 seconds to recognize a fall, but the waiting period can be customized to as little as 10 seconds.</p><p> Medical information and conditions unique to a user&#39;s health history can be plugged into the interface on the paired device. This might be especially useful for elderly populations or people who are medically at a fall risk (think post-surgical or highly medicated patients). However, during testing, after falling on different surfaces, and staying stationary for at least 30 seconds each time, I was never able to trigger the alert system. <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5zYW1zdW5nLmNvbS91cy9zdXBwb3J0L2Fuc3dlci9BTlMwMDA4NzI0NC8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImQ4NzFlMTZhLWE3ZjMtNDQ0Ni1hYmJlLTQyMDQ4M2Y4YzA4OCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAft3ni38Kh5flXwH-YIVN4dYAMaUwzsSO0uGuSuX8J6e&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Fsupport%2Fanswer%2FANS00087244%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.samsung.com/us/support/answer/ANS00087244/">Samsung claims</a> that after a fall, a watch should alert a user for 30 seconds with a popup, sound, and vibration. This delay is supposed to give a user time to get up or cancel the action of alerting emergency services. To be fair, this was also difficult to trigger on the competing Apple Watch Series 8.</p><h2> Customizable fitness regimens </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/7778f1b0-5181-11ee-9f7f-8ab3f3a91b2f" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/7778f1b0-5181-11ee-9f7f-8ab3f3a91b2f" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 face" data-uuid="7fa3dc7b-adbf-303a-9609-4e10e9c59117"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>Making a unique workout plan with key metrics and goals in mind is nothing new for an avid <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-fitness-trackers-133053484.html">fitness junkie</a> . Since the launch of the Galaxy Watch 4, Samsung has made it a point to expand its workout trackers, with over 95 unique exercises and sports to track on the watch face, users can also create their own custom workouts. I regularly start my lift sessions with 45-pound dumbbells. I was able to name this workout in the watch as my deadlift warmup and keep track of the amount of calories burned per session. This focus on customization is not new, though, with competitors like Fitbit and Apple offering similar interfaces in their fitness tracking tools. The ability to create a program to burn a set amount of calories or reach a certain number of steps can be helpful for people like me who like to prefer to count down rather than up.</p><p> Continuing with the theme of customization, <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-galaxy-watches-will-soon-help-you-get-a-better-nights-sleep-130001529.html">Samsung&#39;s new personalized HR zones</a> are meant to help runners better determine how fast to go. The tool is meant to allow users to keep tabs on heart rate zone data and gain insights into personal exertion levels. By staying within specific zones, I can tailor my workout to match my fitness goals, whether it&#39;s fat-burning, endurance improvement, or cardiovascular conditioning. Also, tracking heart rate can help a runner avoid overexertion, which can lead to burnout, or injury. Staying within an appropriate heart rate range ensures a runner is working out safely and sustainably. That all said, again, like most health and fitness features, the benefit of monitoring will come down to discipline. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/b7be9ec0-5184-11ee-aff5-1046c32a663d" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/b7be9ec0-5184-11ee-aff5-1046c32a663d" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 face HR zones." data-uuid="40fdf8f7-c9ed-37ac-b2d3-5a9288e95377"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>I put the feature to the test by setting up my personalized HR zone to a custom bracket that mimics a high-intensity performance, between 165 to 175. When I went on a run, it kept urging me to speed up and buzzed my wrist with the notification that I was below target. And these notifications are no joke. I struggled to reach my target and even when I did, it was mostly luck.</p><p> Running with that much effort, I barely had time to process how to adjust my run according to the alert. So I took a stab at the easiest HR zone target for low-intensity workouts instead at 95 to 105 bpm and found myself struggling with a similar issue-not being able to consistently stay in my target zone. This time, the HR zone alerts were constantly showering me with reminders that I was overexerting and above my HR zone. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/316cfaf0-5185-11ee-bef7-145919d5612d" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/316cfaf0-5185-11ee-bef7-145919d5612d" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="三星 Galaxy Watch 6" data-uuid="b5de28ca-9277-3b78-a484-e360235024ac"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>This is all to say that although it is a nice feature to have if you&#39;re a seasoned athlete and can comprehend and adjust your exertion accordingly. But it&#39;s almost not nearly as beneficial to just get a snapshot overview of where my HR zone naturally is with a given run tracker instead of feeling the constant distracting buzz alerting me to something I&#39;m not sure quite sure what to do with</p><p> Overall, the notification feature is overstimulating. Even when I paused a workout and tried to have a conversation with Cherlynn, the watch kept pinging me to speed up my run, as it continued to monitor my heart rate zone activity and suggest changes even at rest. Despite this one-off, the watch&#39;s sensitivity in terms of auto detection for movement is pretty accurate. It was noticeably faster at recognizing pauses and restarting based on my movement than my Apple Watch, which was often at least a few seconds behind.</p><h2> Sleep tracking and analysis </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/53ad4740-5181-11ee-b9ef-71886e0ed310" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/53ad4740-5181-11ee-b9ef-71886e0ed310" style="height:4000px;width:6000px;" alt="Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 face" data-uuid="67048472-0cf1-33ae-accc-ebe267c445e8"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">马拉克·萨利赫</div></figure><p>Samsung has said it wants to <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-galaxy-watches-will-soon-help-you-get-a-better-nights-sleep-130001529.html">enhance the sleep experience</a> for users by expanding its comprehensive but individualized sleep pattern analysis tools since the last generation. Samsung&#39;s previously announced Sleep Mode features, which automatically disables notifications, dims the watch&#39;s screen, and switches to an invisible infrared LED to minimize distractions. I had no trouble setting up sleep goals and (to my surprise) sleeping with the watch on. It doesn&#39;t suffocate my wrist at night and if anything, is easy to forget it&#39;s on after a while. You can also set up the Smart Things feature, which will detect when a user is sleeping and create the “ideal sleep environment” by turning off or adjusting home electronics like TVs and lights if you&#39;re connected to Samsung home devices. However, I was not able to see how the Watch 6 would interact with smart home gadgets because I don&#39;t personally own any Samsung home devices.</p><p> What I liked about the sleep analysis feature is that after each night of sleep with it on, I got a pretty comprehensive breakdown of how I slept, REM graphic and all, on the Watch 6&#39;s dedicated sleep watch face. I was able to get an even more detailed view of my sleep quality on the phone, which showed me how my nights compared on a day to day, telling me which parts of my REM graphic meant what and why it matters. For example, it broke down how much deep sleep I got and it told me how much more I needed. After sleeping with it for seven nights, you&#39;re supposed to trigger the sleep coach program that also pairs you with your “sleep animal,” a little 2D avatar that is representative of your nighttime habits. And while it was more comfortable than an Apple Watch, I just don&#39;t like the feeling of having something on my wrist at night.</p><h2> The competition </h2><div id="1bdcc9db42f843c28f2944dc2f2c2233"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Az26LyEC8W0?si=x-pPaIcluPI5YCRD" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p> The Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 has emerged as a top choice among Android users, especially at this price point. However, the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-8-real-world-test-130031046-130031250.html">Apple Watch Series 8</a> , which starts at $399, is the obvious alternative for iPhone users. The features are similar, with both models providing GPS tracking, heart-rate sensing, fall detection, sleep tracking and automatic workout recognition.</p><p> In terms of fitness-centric offerings, the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-gps-running-watch-141513957.html">Garmin Forerunner 745</a> , which is on sale for <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Garmin;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4c7f75f5-4803-438a-a506-12a0ccb4ede4&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Garmin&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5nYXJtaW4uY29tL2VuLVVTL3AvNzEzMzYzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJkODcxZTE2YS1hN2YzLTQ0NDYtYWJiZS00MjA0ODNmOGMwODgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAYXm7j9sU2E9IRxxj2m_BDl35u8TV9ct78Aac6mo-KQR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.garmin.com%2Fen-US%2Fp%2F713363" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.garmin.com/en-US/p/713363">$299</a> , might be better suited for athletes seeking comprehensive insights into performance metrics and running-focused training regimens. While it may not be as all-encompassing in terms of health guidance tools, it still includes fundamental features like heart rate monitoring, sleep tracking, stress monitoring, and fall detection.</p><p> But if you want pretty similar offerings in terms of fitness tracking and sleep coaching, the Fitbit Versa 4, which starts at $199, is a pretty cheap alternative. However, with the Versa 4, you get a less integrated smartwatch that feels pretty barebones. For instance, you can&#39;t make or take phone calls or control music through the watch.</p><h2> Wrap-up</h2><p> Samsung has a vision for the Galaxy Watch 6 to be perceived as a health buddy, with all of its dedicated wellness-centric updates in heart health, women&#39;s health, fitness and sleep domains. But the actual benefits come down to the user. Without discipline, there are no insights to be gained, no tracking worthwhile, or coaching that will be accurate.</p><p> But this doesn&#39;t take away from the device&#39;s well-deserved shine in some areas, namely design, comfort and fitness. It&#39;s nothing we have not seen before, and if you already own a wearable of recent vintage, or are an iOS user it&#39;s probably not meant for you. If you have the last-gen Galaxy Watch, then hold on to your money because the updates are already in your pocket.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-galaxy-watch-6-review-evolution-not-revolution-120006375.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/samsungs-galaxy-watch-6-review-evolution-not-revolution-120006375.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> d871e16a-a7f3-4446-abbe-420483f8c088</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 12:00:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694635823</ingested><modified> 2023-09-13T20:10:31+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Health]]></category><category><![CDATA[Fitness]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/53ad4740-5181-11ee-b9ef-71886e0ed310" width="6000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/11e7a990-5181-11ee-9fa7-96ccd067a1d8" width="6000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[                                    Malak Saleh]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 face pictured.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Watch 6 face]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best smart scales for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Data is a useful tool in any battle, especially if you&#39;re opting to wage war against your waistline in an attempt to be healthier. Back in 2007, I bought a dirt-cheap scale and drew my own graph sheets in order to chart my weight&#39;s downward progress after a rough year at university. I think that while 2007 me wouldn&#39;t be pleased with my own fitness journey, he would love the fact that the process is entirely automated, and affordable. Consequently, allow me to take you (and him) on a journey to pick the best smart scale to help you on your own journey toward behavior change and improving your overall health.</p><h2>安全</h2><p>There are valid reasons to weigh yourself, but your self-worth shouldn&#39;t be defined by the number that shows up between your feet. If you&#39;re looking to alter your body shape, that figure could go up as your waistline goes down, since muscle weighs more than fat. Dr. Anne Swift, Director of public health teaching at the University of Cambridge, said that “weighing yourself too often can result in [you] becoming fixated on small fluctuations day-to-day, rather than the overall trend over time.” Swift added that “it&#39;s sometimes better to focus on how clothes fit, or how you feel, rather than your weight.”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> (A meta-analysis from <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26742706/">2016</a> found there may be some negative psychological impact from self weighing. A <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/circ.138.suppl_1.10962">2018 study</a> , however, said that there may be a positive correlation between regular weigh-ins and accelerated weight loss. It can be a minefield, and I&#39;d urge you to take real care of yourself and remember that success won&#39;t happen overnight.)</p><h2> What to look for in a smart scale</h2><h3>重量</h3><p>A weighing scale that weighs you is probably the top requirement, right? One thing to bear in mind is that, with all these measurements, weight readings won&#39;t be as accurate as a calibrated, clinical scale. Consequently, it&#39;s better to focus on the overall full body weight trend up or down over time, rather than the figures in isolation.</p><h3>连接性</h3><p>Most scales will either connect to your phone over Bluetooth, or to your home&#39;s Wi-Fi network, and you should work out your regular weighing routine ahead of time. A lot of lower-end, Bluetooth-only scales will only record your weight when your phone is present and don&#39;t keep local records. That means if you routinely leave your phone outside the bathroom at home, you could lose that day&#39;s stats. Wi-Fi connectivity, on the other hand, allows a scale to post your stats to a server, letting you access them from any compatible device. But you need to be mindful that there&#39;s a small risk to your privacy should that information from your Wi-Fi scale be compromised.</p><h3> Bone density</h3><p> The stronger your bones, the less you&#39;re at risk from breaks and osteoporosis, which you should keep in mind as you get older. Clinical bone density tests use low-power x-rays but higher-end scales can offer an approximation from your own bathroom. These bone mass tests pass a small electrical current through your feet, measuring the resistance as it completes its journey. The resistance offered by bones, fat and muscle are all different, and your scale can identify the difference.</p><h3> Body fat percentage and muscle mass</h3><p> Fat and muscle are necessary parts of our makeup, but an excessive amount of either can be problematic. Much like bone density, a smart scale measures both your body fat and muscle mass percentages using Bioelectrical Impedance Analysis (BIA). This measurement tests how well your body resists the electrical signal passing through your body. (It&#39;s a rough rule of thumb that you should have a 30/70 percent split between fat and muscle, but please consult a medical professional for figures specific to your own body and medical needs.)</p><h3> BMI</h3><p> A lot of scales offer a BMI calculation, and it&#39;s easy to do since you just plot height and weight on a set graph line. Body Mass Index is, however, a problematic measurement that its critics say is both <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2930234/">overly simplistic</a> and often <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.pennmedicine.org/news/news-releases/2013/august/obesitymortality-paradox-demon">greatly misleading</a> . Unfortunately, it&#39;s also one of the most common clinical body metrics and medical professionals will use it to make judgements about your care.</p><h3> Pulse Wave Velocity</h3><p> French health-tech company Withings has offered Pulse Wave Velocity (PWV) on its flagship scale for some time, although regulatory concerns meant it was withdrawn for a period of time. It&#39;s a measurement of arterial stiffness, which acts as a marker both of cardiovascular risk and also other health conditions. I&#39;ve had anecdotal reports that PWV scales have sent people to the doctor, where they&#39;ve found they were close to a cardiac event. It&#39;s worth saying, as with all of these technologies, that there is limited, <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32168728/">albeit positive</a> , research into how accurate these systems are.</p><h3> Display</h3><p> Less a specification and more a note that smart scales have displays ranging from pre-printed LCDs or digital dot matrix layouts through to color screens. On the high end, your scale display can show you trending charts for your weight and other vital statistics, and can even tell you the day&#39;s weather. If you are short-sighted, and plan on weighing yourself first thing in the morning, before you&#39;ve found your glasses / contacts, opt for a big, clear, high-contrast display.</p><h3> App and subscriptions</h3><p> You&#39;ll spend most of your time looking at your health data through its companion app, and it&#39;s vital you get a good one. This includes a clear, clean layout with powerful tools to visualize your progress and analyze your data to look for places you can improve. Given that you often don&#39;t need to buy anything before trying the app, it&#39;s worth testing one or two to see if you vibe with it.</p><p> Several companies also offer premium subscriptions, unlocking other features – including insights and coaching – to go along with your hardware. Fitbit and Withings both offer these services, which you may feel is worth the extra investment each month.</p><h3> Data portability</h3><p> Using the same scale or app platform for years at a time means you&#39;ll build up a massive trove of personal data. And it is, or should be, your right to take that data to another provider when you choose to move platforms in the future. Data portability is, however, a minefield, with different platforms offering wildly different options, making it easy (or hard) to go elsewhere.</p><p> All of the devices in this round-up will allow you to export your data to a .CSV file, which you can then do with as you wish. Importing this information is trickier, with Withings and Garmin allowing it, and Omron, Xiaomi, Eufy and Fitbit not making it that easy. (Apps that engage with Apple Health, meanwhile, can <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N1cHBvcnQuYXBwbGUuY29tL2VuLWdiL2d1aWRlL2lwaG9uZS9pcGg1ZWRlNThjM2QvaW9zIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJiMmFmMmE1Ni1kZTk5LTRhNDMtOGJkOS1kNWU1NzY4MjVlODMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZCtZe_M4AKLG6lYTWvN8T0ow_5B8_ackKhQ43NQGnWK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fen-gb%2Fguide%2Fiphone%2Fiph5ede58c3d%2Fios">output all of your health data</a> in a .XML file.)</p><h3>力量</h3><p>It&#39;s not a huge issue but one worth bearing in mind that each scale will either run disposable batteries (most commonly 4xAAA) or with its own, built-in battery pack. Sadly, all of our crop of smart scales use batteries, adding an environmental and financial cost to your scale life. That&#39;s just about forgivable for scales that cost under $100, but this stretches even to the highest-end models. When you&#39;re spending more than that on a device, the lack of a rechargeable cell feels very, very cheap indeed.</p><h2> The smart scales we tested</h2><p> For this guide, I tested six scales from major manufacturers:</p><h3> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ_n5jXiqBRDOptIAu84EmySDSs5Qwbio4LWHd3rYib8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FXiaomi-Composition-Bluetooth-Statistics-Smartphone%2Fdp%2FB07XNHW2JH">Mi (Xiaomi) Body Composition Scale 2</a> ($29.99) </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/5682ca60-7704-11ed-b7ef-e04eaf660ec8" alt="Stock image of Xiaomi&#39;s Body Comp Scale" data-uuid="836d3451-4913-35c9-ab33-aef32e3c800e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Xiaomi</div></figure><p> Our cheapest model, Xiaomi / Mi&#39;s Body Composition Scale 2 is as bare-bones as you can get, and it shows. It often takes a long while to lock on to get your body weight, and when it does you&#39;ll have to delve into the Zepp Life-branded app in order to look at your extra data. But you can&#39;t fault it for the basics, offering limited weight and body composition for less than the price of a McDonald&#39;s for four.</p><h3> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdedVAmboPWBTWdpUHTI7X3sMt__hDB1_bW8Ef-Yq4yH&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFitbit-FB203BK-Bluetooth-Digital-Weight%2Fdp%2FB07VV6GKDS">Fitbit Aira Air</a> ($49.95) </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/72f09f60-7704-11ed-afdf-974ce8437af6" alt="Image of Fitbit&#39;s Aria Air scale" data-uuid="f28a6a3b-ca2f-31ba-8c83-9e5afab6ac24"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Fitbit</div></figure><p> Fitbit, now part of Google, is the household name for fitness trackers and smartwatches in the US, right? If not, then it must be at least halfway synonymous with it. The Aria Air is the company&#39;s stripped-to-the-bare bones scale, offering your weight and a few other health metrics, but you can trust that Fitbit got the basics right. Not to mention that most of the reason for buying a Fitbit product is to leverage its fitness app anyway.</p><h3> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQkVA5ofcfXgBHkGUcOOXsKMlPTtBM0pu-dOKiWpfQM9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Feufy-Bathroom-Bluetooth-Measurements-Including%2Fdp%2FB09NHR4NX7%2F">Anker Eufy Smart Scale P2 Pro</a> ($79.99) </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/8b138440-7704-11ed-b67f-a253630e349c" alt="Image of Eufy&#39;s P2 Pro smart scale" data-uuid="ebcb8171-9cdf-3cfb-ac5a-f19891d7b618"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Eufy / Anker</div></figure><p> Eufy&#39;s Smart Scale P2 Pro has plenty of things to commend it – the price, the overall look and feel (it&#39;s a snazzy piece of kit) and what it offers. It offers a whole host of in-depth measurements, including Body Fat, Muscle Mass, Water Weight, Body Fat Mass and Bone Mass, as well as calculating things like your Heart Rate and Basal Metabolic Rate (the amount of calories you need to eat a day to not change weight at all) all from inside its app. In fact, buried beneath the friendly graphic, the scale offers a big pile of stats and data that should, I think, give you more than a little coaching on how to improve your lifestyle.</p><p> Shortly before publication, Anker – Eufy&#39;s parent company – was identified as having misled users, and the media, about the security of its products. Its Eufy-branded security cameras, which the company says does not broadcast video outside of your local network, was found to be allowing third parties to access streams online. Consequently, while we have praised the Eufy Smart Scale for its own features, we cannot recommend it without a big caveat.</p><h3> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASi75Tjd0SgYfb-B9rkmhg6WTzW1HyxGlJthfPDFT3f3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOmron-Composition-Monitor-Bluetooth-Connectivity%2Fdp%2FB07WHMBH8K">Omron BCM-500 Body Composition and Scale with Bluetooth</a> ($89.99) </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/b5bb7810-7704-11ed-9bfd-fa2c08b531c4" alt="Image of Omron&#39;s 500 series scale" data-uuid="8c2436d8-674a-3110-b6f3-3748014ca6ec"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Omron</div></figure><p> Given its role in making actual medical devices, you know what you&#39;re getting with an Omron product. A solid, reliable, sturdy, strong (checks the dictionary for more synonyms) dependable piece of kit. There&#39;s no romance or excitement on show, but you can trust that however joyless it may be, it&#39;ll do the job in question and will be user-friendly. The hardware is limited, the app is limited, but it certainly (checks synonyms again) is steady.</p><p> Joking aside, Omron&#39;s Connect app is as bare-bones as you can get, since it acts as an interface for so many of its products. Scroll over to the Weight page, and you&#39;ll get your weight and BMI reading, and if you&#39;ve set a fitness goal, you can see how far you&#39;ve got to go to reach it. You can also switch to seeing a trend graph which, again, offers the most basic visualization on offer.</p><h3> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9HYXJtaW4tV2lyZWxlc3MtQ29ubmVjdGl2aXR5LU1lYXN1cmUtTXVzY2xlL2RwL0IwOEpRUFJOVlg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tY3ItMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImIyYWYyYTU2LWRlOTktNGE0My04YmQ5LWQ1ZTU3NjgyNWU4MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZHC0N0m24_KjtwpGTvy7iEUBJ4c3t1O5sr-aJEhmGpA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGarmin-Wireless-Connectivity-Measure-Muscle%2Fdp%2FB08JQPRNVX">Garmin Index S2</a> ($149.99) </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/cbe09120-7704-11ed-96f7-43fa6701cbfb" alt="Image of Garmin&#39;s Index S2 smart scale" data-uuid="4cf275f1-c12f-3c69-9d86-e251b88a70b3"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Garmin</div></figure><p> Garmin&#39;s got a pretty massive fitness ecosystem of its own, so if you&#39;re already part of that world, its smart bathroom scale is a no-brainer. On one hand, the scale is one of the easiest to use, and most luxurious of the bunch, with its color screen and sleek design. I&#39;m also a big fan of the wealth of data and different metrics the scale throws at you – you can see a full color graph charting your weight progress, and the various metrics it tracks in good detail. If there&#39;s a downside, it&#39;s that Garmin&#39;s setup won&#39;t hold your hand, since it&#39;s for serious fitness people, not newbies.</p><h3> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Withings;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d3b3fb13-488a-4810-a40f-ee84ae8f2918&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Withings&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJkM2IzZmIxMy00ODhhLTQ4MTAtYTQwZi1lZTg0YWU4ZjI5MTgiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2l0aGluZ3MuY29tL3VzL2VuL2JvZHktY29tcCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYjJhZjJhNTYtZGU5OS00YTQzLThiZDktZDVlNTc2ODI1ZTgzIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAc8X9rt-aX4wH02_myPQh5OPGfGfhGCp4LvKeEkxPEmJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.withings.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fbody-comp">Withings Body Comp</a> ($209.95) </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/e0ff36b0-7704-11ed-bbd7-35a0b488360f" alt="Image of Withings&#39; Body Comp" data-uuid="8db1f98c-eef3-334e-93fe-97c1a32c0318"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Withings</div></figure><p> At the highest end, Withings&#39; flagship Body Comp is luxurious, and luxuriously priced, a figure I&#39;d consider to be “too much” to spend on a bathroom scale. For your money, however, you&#39;ll get a fairly comprehensive rundown of body composition metrics including your weight, body fat percentage, vascular age, pulse wave velocity and electrodermal activity. Its monochrome dot matrix display may not be as swish as the Garmin&#39;s, but it refreshes pretty quickly and feels very in-keeping with the hardware&#39;s overall sleek look. If there&#39;s a downside, it&#39;s that they ditched the rechargeable battery found in the Withings Body Cardio (its former flagship, and an excellent scale I&#39;d recommend if it were within the parameters of this guide) in favor of AAA batteries. Which, when you&#39;re spending this much on a scale, makes me feel very nickel-and-dimed.</p><h2> The best cheap smart scale: Fitbit Aria Air, <strong>Mi Body Composition Scale 2</strong> </h2><p><core-commerce id="55f3e395d8e045399b07c9d7af9846d2" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="d0a1eeed3de14400a197c1ab415d1558" data-type="product-list"></p><p> It&#39;s very competitive at the low end for the best budget smart scale, and <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ_n5jXiqBRDOptIAu84EmySDSs5Qwbio4LWHd3rYib8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FXiaomi-Composition-Bluetooth-Statistics-Smartphone%2Fdp%2FB07XNHW2JH">Xiaomi</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdedVAmboPWBTWdpUHTI7X3sMt__hDB1_bW8Ef-Yq4yH&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFitbit-FB203BK-Bluetooth-Digital-Weight%2Fdp%2FB07VV6GKDS">Fitbit</a> offer dramatically contrasting products for a very low price. Fitbit&#39;s scale has far fewer features, but has better build quality, is faster and more reliable than its cheaper rival. Crucially, it also leverages the Fitbit app, which is refined and easy-to-use, offering clean, easy-to understand visualizations.</p><p> Xiaomi, meanwhile, offers weight and some basic body composition measurements, although this extra data is only visualized inside the app. From a data perspective, the Xiaomi has the edge, but its companion app – formerly Mi Fit, now branded as Zepp Life – is terrible. The lag time for each weigh-in, too, leaves a lot to be desired with the Xiaomi, although I had no qualms about its accuracy.</p><p> When I was a kid, and complained about something, my nan would say “look, you can either have a first class walk or a third class ride.” And Fitbit&#39;s scale here is the very definition of a first class ride – polished, snappy and with a world-class app by its side. The Xiaomi, meanwhile, offers more for your money, and charges less, but both hardware and software lack any sort of polish. It&#39;s therefore up to you if you&#39;d rather the first class walk or the third class ride.</p><h2> The best scale for people who want features (and aren&#39;t fussed about security): Eufy&#39;s P2 Pro</h2><p><core-commerce id="94d71cfa25df4515a885442682d0b1e9" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Well, this is awkward. Not long before this guide was published, it was revealed that <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQkVA5ofcfXgBHkGUcOOXsKMlPTtBM0pu-dOKiWpfQM9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Feufy-Bathroom-Bluetooth-Measurements-Including%2Fdp%2FB09NHR4NX7%2F">Eufy</a> is in the midst of a massive security issue. Researchers found that its security cameras, which were promised to be secure, allowed internet users to access the stream using VLC player. Consequently the high praise for Eufy&#39;s P2 Pro I have as a scale will need to be moderated by the fact that we don&#39;t yet know how deep the company&#39;s promises around privacy and security really run.</p><p> It&#39;s unfortunate, as the scale does leap head-and-shoulders above the competition at this level, and it surpassed my expectations by quite a bit. The ease of use was one thing, but the depth of metric data made available in the app, and the way it presents that information, is fantastic. While I don&#39;t think the Eufy Life app is better than, say, Withings&#39; class-leading Health Mate, it offers exactly what a would-be weight-watcher would need.</p><p> The fact you can get plenty of your vital statistics graphed by hitting two buttons helps you visualize your progress, but the stat dashboard laying out everything, including your BMR, is so useful. If you&#39;re going all Quantified Self, you could theoretically calculate your daily calorie intake to the finest of fine margins looking at this thing every morning.</p><h2> The best scale for athletes: Garmin Index S2</h2><p><core-commerce id="affb9482d05c466385eb81b42f862de2" data-type="product-list"></p><p> I&#39;m very partial to <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9HYXJtaW4tV2lyZWxlc3MtQ29ubmVjdGl2aXR5LU1lYXN1cmUtTXVzY2xlL2RwL0IwOEpRUFJOVlg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tY3ItMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImIyYWYyYTU2LWRlOTktNGE0My04YmQ5LWQ1ZTU3NjgyNWU4MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZHC0N0m24_KjtwpGTvy7iEUBJ4c3t1O5sr-aJEhmGpA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGarmin-Wireless-Connectivity-Measure-Muscle%2Fdp%2FB08JQPRNVX">Garmin&#39;s Index S2</a> , but I also think it&#39;s the sort of scale that needs to be used by people who know what they&#39;re doing. Almost everything about the hardware is spot-on, and the only fly in its ointment is the low refresh rate on its color screen. I can&#39;t say how upsetting it was to see the display refresh in such a laggy, unpolished manner, especially when you&#39;re spending this much money. But that&#39;s my only complaint, and the rest of the hardware (and software) is otherwise pitch-perfect. If you&#39;re looking to set goals to alter your body shape, this probably isn&#39;t the scale for you – it&#39;s the scale you buy once you already calculate your BMR on a daily basis.</p><h2> The best scale for the worried well: Withings Body Comp</h2><p><core-commerce id="9df2564d1e734471bb0e6c6373a5e3ca" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Naturally, if you&#39;re looking for a machine that&#39;ll cater to your every whim and hypochondriac urge, then <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Withings;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d3b3fb13-488a-4810-a40f-ee84ae8f2918&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Withings&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJkM2IzZmIxMy00ODhhLTQ4MTAtYTQwZi1lZTg0YWU4ZjI5MTgiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2l0aGluZ3MuY29tL3VzL2VuL2JvZHktY29tcCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYjJhZjJhNTYtZGU5OS00YTQzLThiZDktZDVlNTc2ODI1ZTgzIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAc8X9rt-aX4wH02_myPQh5OPGfGfhGCp4LvKeEkxPEmJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.withings.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fbody-comp">Withings&#39; Body Comp</a> is the way forward. It&#39;s a luxury scale in every sense of the word, and you should appreciate the level of polish and technology on show here. Apart from the batteries, which I&#39;ve already said is a cheap and nasty way to save money given that you&#39;re dropping this much money on a product.</p><p> The group of people who think it&#39;s reasonable to spend $200 on a scale is, especially with food and energy prices spiking, a fairly small one. But if you&#39;re the sort who already spends hand over fist to keep your body in check, this is probably justifiable as an “investment.” Knowing all of the extras about your nerve health and arteries is a bonus, but let&#39;s be clear and say this isn&#39;t the top pick for everybody. Hell, you might have second thoughts even if you do have a subscription to Good Yachting Magazine.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-scale-160033523.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-scale-160033523.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> b2af2a56-de99-4a43-8bd9-d5e576825e83</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 11:50:02 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694692202</ingested><modified> 2023-09-14T11:50:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="4160" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/e83a6d00-7af6-11ed-bffb-35bef259a819" width="6240"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4160" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/e83a6d00-7af6-11ed-bffb-35bef259a819" width="6240"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[PonyWang via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[woman weighing on scale to measure her weight]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[closeup of weighing on scale]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tesla gets $160 million in EU funding to expand its Supercharger network in 22 countries]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> The European Union (EU) is providing €352 million ($378 million) in <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://cinea.ec.europa.eu/news-events/news/transport-infrastructure-over-eur-352-million-eu-funding-boost-greener-mobility-2023-09-11_en">funding</a> to support green transport infrastructure, and Tesla will get a large chunk of that money. The company&#39;s Polish and Italian divisions will receive a total of €148.72 million ($159.64 million) to install or upgrade 7,198 Superchargers across 22 countries, according to the EU&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://cinea.ec.europa.eu/system/files/2023-09/CEF-T-2021-AFIF_Cut-off%204_List%20of%20projects_FINAL_0.pdf">list of projects</a> .</p><p> &quot;The project aims at deploying 6,458 recharging points (250 kW) for LDV in 613 locations in 16 countries (AT, BE, BG, DE, ES, FI, FR, IE, IT, LV, LT, LU, NL, RO, SK, SE) along the Core and Comprehensive Network. The project foresees both the deployment of new recharging stations and the replacement of existing outdated recharging points not satisfying the requirement of the call in terms of recharging capacity and open-accessibility,&quot; the Tesla Italy project description reads. It states the same for Poland&#39;s Tesla division, while adding an additional six nations (CZ, EL, HR, HU, PL, SI).</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Proposals for the project had an April 13, 2023 deadline, and the EU just announced the successful bids. It appears to cover a large chunk of Europe, but there are no details on a breakdown of new stations or upgrades yet. Much of the funding could go toward updates to Tesla&#39;s Supercharger V4, which offers a <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://electrek.co/2023/07/26/tesla-confirms-supercharger-v4-350-kw-output/">power output of 350 kW</a> — up from the <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-07-18-tesla-opens-vegas-v3-supercharger-station.html">last model&#39;s 250 kW</a> .</p><p> Tesla recently celebrated its 10,000th individual Supercharger connector in the EU, and counts 875 stations in total. The following is a <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://insideevs.com/news/614547/tesla-10000-superchargers-europe/">breakdown</a> for the top countries: Germany (143), France (123), the UK (100), Norway (95), Sweden (65), Italy (59), Spain (50), the Netherlands (39), Austria (27) and Switzerland (27).</p><p> It&#39;s a large percentage of funding for one company, but the EU&#39;s decision seems logical. Other car companies including <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ford-ev-drivers-will-get-access-to-12000-north-american-tesla-superchargers-next-spring-221752191.html">Ford</a> , GM, <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/volvo-is-the-latest-automaker-to-adopt-teslas-ev-charging-standard-191942675.html">Volvo</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-will-use-teslas-ev-charging-standard-on-north-american-cars-161547427.html">Mercedes</a> have said they&#39;ll switch to Tesla&#39;s North American Charging Standard (NACS) port, and struck deals with the company to use its Superchargers — meaning a lot of drivers will be able to access Tesla&#39;s network. <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tesla-superchargers-other-evs-france-norway-pilot-152019187.html">Early in 2021</a> , Tesla <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.tesla.com/support/non-tesla-supercharging">opened up its network</a> to all EV users at select Superchargers in the Netherlands, France and Norway.</p><p> The EU greenlit 26 projects in total, with most dedicated to EV charging points but several relating to hydrogen refueling stations for heavy duty and other types of vehicles. &quot;Our investment of €352 million will translate into approximately 12,000 charging points, 18 hydrogen refueling stations, and the electrification of ports and airports, including the port of Rotterdam and 37 Spanish airports,&quot; said European Commissioner for Transport Adina Vălean.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/tesla-gets-160-million-in-eu-funding-to-expand-its-supercharger-network-in-22-countries-114545141.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/tesla-gets-160-million-in-eu-funding-to-expand-its-supercharger-network-in-22-countries-114545141.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 851e9559-b16e-4854-8d79-741a70e2e089</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 14 Sep 2023 11:45:45 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694691052</ingested><modified> 2023-09-14T11:31:02+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="2662" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/24dbfb20-52ec-11ee-95e9-e63cd3128092" width="3994"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2662" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/24dbfb20-52ec-11ee-95e9-e63cd3128092" width="3994"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[BARCELONA, SPAIN - May 19: A Tesla Supercharger, a 480-volt direct current fast-charging technology by the American multinational automotive and clean energy company that manufactures all-electric vehicles, exhibited on their stand during the Automobile Barcelona International Motor Show on May 19, 2023, in Barcelona, Spain. (Photo by Joan Cros/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Automobile Barcelona International Motor Show]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: Hacking a Vegas casino may just take a single phone call]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> The ALPHV/BlackCat ransomware group claimed responsibility for the MGM Resorts cyber outage on Tuesday, and it apparently took the group <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hackers-claim-it-only-took-a-10-minute-phone-call-to-shutdown-mgm-resorts-143147493.html">only 10 minutes</a> on a phone call to glean the information needed to shut down systems and slot machines — not the slot machines! — at casinos owned by MGM Resorts.</p><p> “All ALPHV ransomware group did to compromise MGM Resorts was hop on LinkedIn, find an employee, then call the Help Desk,” the organization wrote in a post on X. Those details came from ALPHV but have not been independently confirmed by security researchers.</p><p> MGM Resorts didn&#39;t respond to a request for comment but said on Tuesday that “Our resorts, including dining, entertainment and gaming, are currently operational.”</p><p> — 马特·史密斯</p><p></p><h3>The biggest stories you might